Air Vice Marshal (retd.) '''Fakhrul Azam''', ndc, psc was the [[Chief of Air Staff (Bangladesh)|Chief of the Air Staff]] of [[Bangladesh Air Force]] from 2002 to 2007. He studied in the prestigious [[PAF College Sargodha|Sargodha College]] of [[Pakistan Air Force]]. He was in the '''Tempest''' house (694-T). He left the institution in 1965 after completing his [[Senior Cambridge]]. He was commissioned in the Pakistan Air Force on 13 March 1971 from the 51st GD(P) Course. Fakhrul was appointed as the 'Chief of the Air Staff of Bangladesh Air Force' on 8 April 2002 by then-Prime Minister [[Khaleda Zia]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/107977/Khaleda-hosts-iftar-for-professionals |title=Khaleda hosts iftar for professionals |publisher=En.prothom-alo.com |date=2016-06-12 |accessdate=2016-07-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2007/04/10/d7041001085.htm |title=The Daily Star Web Edition Vol. 5 Num 1016 |publisher=Archive.thedailystar.net |date= |accessdate=2016-07-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Star Report |url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2006/04/25/d6042501022.htm |title=The Daily Star Web Edition Vol. 5 Num 677 |publisher=Archive.thedailystar.net |date= |accessdate=2016-07-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=UNB, Jessore |url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/2003/12/31/d31231100167.htm |title=The Daily Star Web Edition Vol. 4 Num 213 |publisher=Archive.thedailystar.net |date=2003-12-31 |accessdate=2016-07-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2006/04/05/air-chief-fakhrul-azam-gets-one-yr-extension |title=Air chief Fakhrul Azam gets one yr extension |publisher=bdnews24.com |date=2006-04-05 |accessdate=2016-07-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baf.mil.bd/new/aboutbaf/formercoas.html |title=Bangladesh Air Force |publisher=Baf.mil.bd |date= |accessdate=2016-07-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://pafcollegesargodha.com/pages/display/64|title=PAF College Sargodha: Illustrious Students.|